	<convention xml:id="contributed-talk-2b">
		<title>The Weighted Spanning Tree Enumerator of Multi-Partite Graphs</title>
		<p><dl>
			<li><title>Zander Rasmussen</title> <p>Willamette University</p></li>
			<li><title>Peter Otto</title> <p>Willamette University</p></li>
		</dl></p>
		<p>The weighted spanning tree enumerator (WSTE) is the sum of weights of all spanning trees of a graph.  A recent result expressed the WSTE of multi-partite graphs in terms of the WSTE of its partition graph, which greatly simplifies the computation of the WSTE of the original graph.  The proof to this result is algebraic, using the Weighted Matrix Tree Theorem.  In this talk, we will present the new result and the work we have done in deriving a graph theoretic justification for the result. </p>
	</convention>

	<convention xml:id="contributed-talk-3a">
