	<convention xml:id="contributed-talk-3b">
		<title>Geodesics and hyperbolicity for half-plane models of taxicab hyperbolic space</title>
		<p><dl>
			<li><title>Alina Potapyev</title> <p>Seattle University</p></li>
			<li><title>Dylan Helliwell</title> <p>Seattle University, Faculty</p></li>
			<li><title>Luka Lawrence</title> <p>Seattle University, Undergraduate Student</p></li>
			<li><title>Kevin Lin</title> <p>Seattle University, Undergraduate Student</p></li>
		</dl></p>
		<p>We develop new geometric spaces by blending the half-plane model for the hyperbolic plane with taxicab geometry. Starting with a taxicab norm on each tangent space, the lengths of curves are analyzed, allowing us to determine geodesics, and from these, a distance function. Then we show that these spaces are hyperbolic in the sense of Gromov.</p>
	</convention>

